()methods of privileged accounts:-

1️⃣ Access Request / Approval Methods:-
Ye methods privileged (admin) access ko manage aur approve karne ke liye hote hain.
Ye usually AccessRequestManager / PrivilegedAccessService class ke andar aate hain.
(a).requestPrivilegedAccess(user, resource, duration):-
Kya karta hai: User temporary access request karta hai kisi resource ya role ke liye.
Class: PrivilegedAccessService ya AccessRequestManager

Example:-
String requestId = accessService.requestPrivilegedAccess("dev01", "DB_Admin", 2);
System.out.println("Access request created: " + requestId);

Output:-
Access request created: REQ-1001
------------------------------------
(b)approvePrivilegedAccess(requestId, approver):-
Kya karta hai: Manager ya system request approve karta hai.
Class: PrivilegedAccessService

approvePrivilegedAccess("REQ-1001", "manager01");
System.out.println("Request REQ-1001 approved by manager01");

Output Example:-
Request REQ-1001 approved by manager01
------------------------------------------------
()denyPrivilegedAccess(requestId, approver):-
Kya karta hai: Manager request reject karta hai.
Class: PrivilegedAccessService

denyPrivilegedAccess("REQ-1002", "manager01");
System.out.println("Request REQ-1002 denied by manager01");

Output Example:-
Request REQ-1002 denied by manager01
-------------------------------------------------------
()grantJustInTimeAccess(user, role, duration):-
Kya karta hai: Temporary access provide karta hai (Just In Time access).
Class: PrivilegedAccessService

grantJustInTimeAccess("dev01", "DB_Admin", 2);
System.out.println("DB_Admin role granted to dev01 for 2 hours");

Output Example:-
DB_Admin role granted to dev01 for 2 hours
----------------------------------------------

---------------------------------------------
2️⃣ Role & Policy Management:-

()createPrivilegedRole(roleName, permissions):-
