6️⃣ complianceCheckPrivilegedAccounts():-
Ye method sab privileged accounts ke compliance status check karta hai.
Compliance matlab: account rules/regulations follow kar raha hai ya nahi (SOX/GDPR/HIPAA etc.).

Parameters:-
None (ye method generally sab accounts ko check karta hai)
Class: ComplianceService / AuditService
------------------
7️⃣ flagNonCompliantActivity(activity):-
Kya karta hai: Agar koi activity rules violate kare(jaise unauthorized delete, data leak),
to flag aur alert generate karta hai.
Class: ComplianceService / AuditService

Code Example:-
public void flagNonCompliantActivity(String activity) {
    System.out.println("Non-compliant activity flagged: " + activity);
}
Usage & Output:-
complianceService.flagNonCompliantActivity("dev01 deleted critical DB table");

Output:-
Non-compliant activity flagged: dev01 deleted critical DB table
------------------
8️⃣ Emergency / Break Glass Access Methods:-
Ye methods emergency ke liye privileged access provide aur track karte hain.

(a)enableBreakGlassAccess(user, system, duration):-
Kya karta hai: Emergency ke liye full access temporary enable karta hai.
Class: PrivilegedAccessService / BreakGlassManager
public void enableBreakGlassAccess(String user, String system, int durationHours) {
    System.out.println("Break glass access enabled for " + user + " on " + system + " for " + durationHours + " hour(s)");
}

Output Example:-
Break glass access enabled for admin01 on DB_Server1 for 1 hour(s)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
(b)disableBreakGlassAccess(user, system):-
Kya karta hai: Emergency access revoke karta hai.
Class: PrivilegedAccessService / BreakGlassManager

public void disableBreakGlassAccess(String user, String system) {
    System.out.println("Break glass access revoked for " + user + " on " + system);
}

Output Example:-
Break glass access revoked for admin01 on DB_Server1
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
(c)logBreakGlassUsage(user, system, reason):-
Kya karta hai: Emergency access ka reason aur usage log karta hai for audit.
Class: AuditService / BreakGlassManager

public void logBreakGlassUsage(String user, String system, String reason) {
    System.out.println("Break glass usage logged for audit: User=" + user + ", System=" + system + ", Reason=" + reason);
}

Output Example:-
Break glass usage logged for audit: User=admin01, System=DB_Server1, Reason=Emergency data recovery
----------------------------------------------------
Service accounts 
()Service Account kya hai?
Definition:-
Service account ek special type ka account hota hai jo human user ke liye nahi,
balki applications, services, ya automated processes ke liye banaya jata hai.
Matlab, ye account machine-to-machine communication ke liye hota hai,
jaise ek program doosre program ke saath interact kare.
Iska use automated tasks, scripts, cron jobs, APIs, ya background services ke liye hota hai.
----------------
()Service Account ke Features:-
()Non-human account:-
Iska use log nahi karte, sirf systems aur apps use karte hain.

()Fixed permissions:-
Ye account usually restricted permissions ke saath aata hai.
Principle: “Least Privilege” — sirf wo access jo kaam ke liye zaroori hai.

()Automation ke liye:-
Example:
Backup scripts ke liye DB access
API calls from one system to another
CI/CD pipelines ke liye deployment

()Credentials / Secrets:-
Iske paas username/password, API token, or certificate ho sakta hai.
Ye credentials vaults me secure store karna best practice hai.

()Audit & Monitoring:-
Service accounts ko monitor karna aur log maintain karna important hai.
Unauthorized activity ya misuse detect karne ke liye logs aur alerts maintain karte hain.

1️⃣ Service Account Class
import java.util.*;

class ServiceAccount {
    String name;
    String system;
    String role;
    String password;
    boolean active;

    public ServiceAccount(String name, String system, String role, String password) {
        this.name = name;
        this.system = system;
        this.role = role;
        this.password = password;
        this.active = true;
    }

    public void deactivate() {
        this.active = false;
        System.out.println("Service account " + name + " deactivated");
    }
}

2️⃣ Service Account Manager (IAM / PAM)
class ServiceAccountManager {

    Map<String, ServiceAccount> accounts = new HashMap<>();

    // Create service account
    public void createServiceAccount(String name, String system, String role, String password) {
        ServiceAccount sa = new ServiceAccount(name, system, role, password);
        accounts.put(name, sa);
        System.out.println("Service account created: " + name);
    }

    // Rotate password
    public void rotatePassword(String name, String newPassword) {
        ServiceAccount sa = accounts.get(name);
        if(sa != null) {
            sa.password = newPassword;
            System.out.println("Password rotated for service account: " + name);
        } else {
            System.out.println("Service account not found: " + name);
        }
    }

    // Deactivate service account
    public void deactivateServiceAccount(String name) {
        ServiceAccount sa = accounts.get(name);
        if(sa != null) sa.deactivate();
        else System.out.println("Service account not found: " + name);
    }

    // Monitor activity (dummy example)
    public void monitorActivity(String name, String activity) {
        ServiceAccount sa = accounts.get(name);
        if(sa != null) {
            System.out.println("Activity logged for " + name + ": " + activity);
        } else {
            System.out.println("Service account not found: " + name);
        }
    }
}
3️⃣ Example Usage with Output
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ServiceAccountManager sam = new ServiceAccountManager();

        // 1️⃣ Create service accounts
        sam.createServiceAccount("DB_BackupService", "DB_Server1", "DB_ReadOnly", "Pass@123");
        sam.createServiceAccount("CI_CD_Service", "Jenkins_Server", "Build_Deploy", "Jenkins@456");

        // 2️⃣ Rotate password
        sam.rotatePassword("DB_BackupService", "NewPass@789");

        // 3️⃣ Monitor activity
        sam.monitorActivity("DB_BackupService", "Backup job started at 03:00 AM");
        sam.monitorActivity("CI_CD_Service", "Deployment executed for ProjectX");

        // 4️⃣ Deactivate service account
        sam.deactivateServiceAccount("CI_CD_Service");
    }
}

Expected Output:-
Service account created: DB_BackupService
Service account created: CI_CD_Service
Password rotated for service account: DB_BackupService
Activity logged for DB_BackupService: Backup job started at 03:00 AM
Activity logged for CI_CD_Service: Deployment executed for ProjectX
Service account CI_CD_Service deactivated

()1️⃣ createServiceAccount():-
Purpose: Service account banata hai aur IAM / PAM system me register karta hai.
ye ServiceAccountManager class ka method hai.
Parameters:-
name → Account ka naam (jaise "DB_BackupService")
system → Target system (jaise "DB_Server1")
role → Assigned role (jaise "DB_ReadOnly")
password → Initial password / credentials
Output Example:-
Service account created: DB_BackupService

2️⃣ rotatePassword():-
Purpose: Service account ke credentials update karta hai (password rotate karna) for security.
ye ServiceAccountManager class ka method hai.
Parameters:-
name → Account name
newPassword → Naya password
💡 Use Case:-
Security best practice ke liye regular password rotation, vault integration ke saath.

3️⃣ monitorActivity():-
Purpose: Service account ka activity log karta hai, audit aur monitoring ke liye.
()ye ServiceAccountManager class ka method hai.
Parameters:-
name → Account name
activity → Activity description (e.g., "Backup job started at 03:00 AM")

Output Example:-
Activity logged for DB_BackupService: Backup job started at 03:00 AM
💡 Use Case:-
Unauthorized activity detect karne ke liye, auditing aur compliance reporting ke liye.

4️⃣ deactivateServiceAccount():-
Purpose: Agar service account unnecessary ya compromised ho, to disable karta hai.
()ye ServiceAccountManager class ka method hai.
Parameters:-
name → Account name

Output Example:-
Service account DB_BackupService deactivated

💡 Use Case:-
Unused accounts disable karna, security risk kam karne ke liye.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
()deactivate():-
ServiceAccount:-Service account object ka status inactive karna
ye ServiceAccount Class ke method hai.
-----------------------------------------------
()elevated accounts kya hai?
--elevated accounts basically wo accounts hote hain jinke paas normal user se zyada privileges hote hain.
Ye accounts system me powerful access rakhte hain, jaise ki admin ya superuser.
Agar galat haath me chale, to system compromise ho sakta hai.

()🔹 Elevated Accounts Types:-

Admin Accounts:-
Full control over systems
Example: Windows me Administrator, Linux me root

Service Accounts:-
Applications ya scripts ke liye special access
Example: Database backup account, API service account

Privileged User Accounts:-
Certain tasks ke liye zyada rights
Example: Network admin, Security admin
---------------------------------------
()🔹 IAM me Elevated Account Governance:-
SailPoint ya kisi IAM me elevated accounts ke liye:-

Discovery / Inventory:-
Kaunse elevated accounts exist karte hain
Example: Active Directory + DB Admin accounts

Access Request / Approval:-
Normal user direct elevated access nahi le sakta
Manager / Security approval required

Just-in-Time Access (JIT):-
Temporary elevated access diya jata hai
Expire hone ke baad access automatically revoke

Audit / Monitoring:-
Who did what, kab kiya
Logging & alerts for suspicious activity

Policy Enforcement:-
MFA mandatory
Strong password policies
Segregation of duties
---------------------------------------
()Elevated access review kya hai?
--Elevated Access Review (EAR) ek process hai jisme privileged / elevated accounts ka access review kiya jata hai.
Purpose: Ensure ki sirf authorized log hi sensitive systems pe access le rahe hain.

()Purpose of Elevated Access Review
Compliance:-
Regulatory requirements follow karna (SOX, GDPR, HIPAA)
Example: SOX audit me auditors check karte hain ki sirf authorized log hi finance systems access kar rahe hain

()Security:-
Unauthorized access detect karna
Risk kam karna (ex: someone misusing admin rights)

()Access Management:-
Ensure ki temporary privileged access expire ho gaya hai
Just-in-time (JIT) access ka review.

()Review access:-
Managers / application owners verify karte hain ki user ka access still needed hai agar nahi toh
Revoke unnecessary access,
---------------------------methods of elevated access review:->>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
()1️⃣ listElevatedUsers():-
public void listElevatedUsers() {
    for(String user : elevatedUsers.keySet())
        System.out.println(user + " - Role: " + elevatedUsers.get(user));
}
Purpose: Sab elevated / privileged users ko list karna for review.
Parameters: None
Output Example:-
Elevated users review:
admin01 - Role: DB_Admin
dev01 - Role: Server_Root
ops01 - Role: Cloud_Admin
What it does:-
IAM me registered high-privilege accounts ko fetch karke display karta hai,
Review ke liye manager ya auditor ke samne list ready karta hai.
------------------------------
()2️⃣ revokeAccess(user):-
public void revokeAccess(String user) {
    if(elevatedUsers.containsKey(user)) { elevatedUsers.remove(user); System.out.println("Elevated access revoked for " + user); }
}
Purpose: Agar kisi user ka elevated access unnecessary ya risky hai, to revoke karna
Parameters:-
--user → Account name (String)

Output Example:-
Elevated access revoked for dev01

What it does:-
User ka elevated access remove karta hai
IAM/PAM me permissions update kar deta hai
Audit log ke liye entry bhi generate hoti hai.
--------------------------------------------------
()3️⃣ extendJITAccess(user, hours):-
public void extendJITAccess(String user, int hours) {
    if(elevatedUsers.containsKey(user)) System.out.println("JIT access extended for " + user + " by " + hours + " hours");
}
Purpose: Temporary Just-in-Time access extend karta hai.
Purpose: Temporary / Just-in-Time access ko extend karna

Parameters:-
--user → Account name (String)

--hours → Additional duration (int)

Output Example:-
JIT access extended for admin01 by 2 hours

What it does:-
JIT (temporary) elevated access ka duration increase karta hai
Normally short-term access ke liye use hota hai.
-------------------------------------------------
()4️⃣ reviewAccessHistory(user):-
public void reviewAccessHistory(String user) {
    System.out.println("Access history for " + user + ": (example logs here)");
}
Purpose: User ke elevated access ke past activity / usage history review karna

Parameters:-
--user → Account name (String)

Output Example:-
Access history for admin01:
- 2026-03-10 09:00 AM: Logged in DB_Server1
- 2026-03-11 11:30 AM: Modified user roles

What it does:-
Audit & compliance ke liye detailed log provide karta hai
Detect unauthorized or risky activity
-----------------------------------------------
()5️⃣ flagNonCompliantUser(user, reason):-
public void flagNonCompliantUser(String user, String reason) {
    System.out.println("Non-compliant elevated user flagged: " + user + " - Reason: " + reason);
}
Purpose: Rules violate karne wale user ko flag karta hai.
Purpose: Agar user rules violate kare (ex: unnecessary admin rights), to flag karna

Parameters:-
--user → Account name

--reason → Violation ka reason (String)

Output Example:-
Non-compliant elevated user flagged: dev01 - Reason: Unnecessary root access

What it does:-
Security team ko alert karta hai
Audit trail maintain karta hai
--------------------------------------------------
()6️⃣ generateElevatedAccessReport(timePeriod):-
public void generateElevatedAccessReport(String timePeriod) {
    System.out.println("Elevated Access Report (" + timePeriod + "): (example report)");
}
Purpose: Elevated access ka summary report generate karta hai.
Parameters:-
--timePeriod → Period string (ex: "Last Month")

Output Example:-
