()7️⃣ approveElevatedAccessRequest(requestId, approver):-
public void approveElevatedAccessRequest(String requestId, String approver) {
    System.out.println("Elevated access request #" + requestId + " approved by " + approver);
}
Purpose: Elevated access request approve karta hai.
Purpose: Elevated access request ko approve karna

Parameters:-

--requestId → Request unique ID

--approver → Manager / owner name

Output Example:-
Elevated access request #123 approved by manager01

What it does:-
User ko temporary elevated access deta hai
Approval workflow maintain karta hai
-----------------------------------------------------------
()8️⃣ denyElevatedAccessRequest(requestId, approver):-
public void denyElevatedAccessRequest(String requestId, String approver) {
    System.out.println("Elevated access request #" + requestId + " denied by " + approver);
}
Purpose: Elevated access request reject karna

Parameters:-
--requestId → Request ID

--approver → Manager / owner name

Output Example:-
Elevated access request #124 denied by manager02

What it does:-
Unauthorized or unnecessary requests ko reject karta hai
Security aur compliance maintain hoti hai.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
()9️⃣ auditElevatedAccess(user, timePeriod):-
public void auditElevatedAccess(String user, String timePeriod) {
    System.out.println("Audit log for " + user + " (" + timePeriod + "): (example logs)");
}
Purpose: Specific user ka elevated access audit karta hai
Purpose: Specific user ke elevated access ka audit log review

Parameters:-
--user → Account name
--timePeriod → Time frame

Output Example:-
Audit log for admin01 (Last Week):
- 03/10 09:00 AM: DB login
- 03/11 02:00 PM: Updated server config

What it does:-
Compliance audits ke liye detailed user activity track karta hai
Detect suspicious or unauthorized actions
